{
  "texts": [
    "In a recent publication, Zhao et al.",
    "introduced a machine learning algorithm named CLEAN (Comparative Learning-enabled Enzyme Annotation), designed to predict enzyme functions from amino acid sequence characterizations.",
    "This innovative approach is applicable even for enzymes that have hitherto been unexplored or poorly understood [13].",
    "Although some of these models based on protein sequence representation have achieved extremely high prediction accuracy [10], only few ML algorithms tried to study enzymatic function from the perspective of chemical reactions waiting to be catalyzed.",
    "The assignment of Enzyme Commission (EC) numbers to enzymatic reactions is an arduous and continual task that necessitates the perpetual generation and refinement of rules by domain experts."
  ]
}